name: Triceps extension
description: An isolation exercise targeting the triceps muscle by extending the arm at the elbow joint.

name: Pushdown
description: A cable-based exercise that targets the triceps by pushing a bar or rope downward.

name: Dips
description: A compound push exercise that targets the chest, shoulders, and triceps by lowering and raising the body using parallel bars.

name: Close-grip bench press
description: A variation of the bench press focusing on the triceps by using a narrower grip.

name: Squat
description: A compound exercise targeting the quads, hamstrings, and glutes by mimicking the motion of sitting in a chair.

name: Lunge
description: A lower-body exercise targeting the quads, hamstrings, and glutes, performed by stepping forward into a split stance.

name: Leg press
description: A compound exercise where the individual pushes a weight away from them using their legs.

name: Leg extension
description: An isolation exercise targeting the quadriceps muscles by extending the leg at the knee.

name: Frog jumping
description: A plyometric exercise where the individual jumps into the air in a squat position, resembling a frog jump.

name: Calf raise
description: An isolation exercise targeting the calf muscles, performed by raising the heels off the ground.

name: Aerobics
description: A form of physical exercise that combines rhythmic activity with stretching and strength training routines.

name: Circuit training
description: A form of resistance training using high-intensity aerobics targeting strength building and muscular endurance.

name: Cycling
description: A cardiovascular exercise involving riding a bicycle, either stationary or moving.

name: Hiking
description: A long, vigorous walk, usually on trails in the countryside.

name: Power walking
description: A walking technique emphasizing speed and arm motion.

name: Running
description: A method of terrestrial locomotion allowing humans to move rapidly on foot.

name: Skipping rope
description: A cardiovascular exercise where an individual jumps over a swinging rope.

name: Swimming
description: An activity using the limbs to move through water, providing both muscular strength and endurance workouts.

name: Walking
description: A form of exercise involving a steady, brisk walk, beneficial for cardiovascular health.

name: Sprinting
description: Running over a short distance in a limited period of time, emphasizing speed.

name: Crunch
description: A core exercise targeting the abdominal muscles by curling the shoulders towards the pelvis.

name: Leg raise
description: An exercise targeting the lower abdominal muscles by lifting the legs towards the torso.

name: Russian Twist
description: A core exercise where an individual twists the torso while holding a weight, targeting oblique muscles.

name: Sit-up
description: A core exercise involving lifting the torso towards the knees, targeting the abdominal muscles.

name: Biceps curl
description: An isolation exercise targeting the biceps muscles by curling a weight towards the shoulder.

name: Pull ups with supinated grip
description: A compound exercise where the individual pulls themselves up using an underhand grip, emphasizing the biceps and back muscles.
